      <div class="generic-block">
        <h3>Our Reimbursement Philosophy</h3>

        <p>Here are a few key points to get the conversation started:</p>

        <p><strong><u>General Reimbursement</u></strong>: In the first year, reimbursement is based on a fee-for-service model. But, once we have data about our members and their needs, we will add quality incentives and move towards alternative payment models. This will allow better alignment between reimbursement and our shared objective of improved clinical outcomes.</p>

        <p><strong><u>Care Coordination Reimbursement</u></strong>: We understand coordination of care is increasingly complex, and you need support.&nbsp; To reinforce physician involvement in care transitions and episodic care, we reimburse for:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Telephone Evaluation and Management Services</li>
          <li>On-line Evaluation and Management Service</li>
          <li>Transitional Care Management Services</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong><u>Counseling and Risk Factor Reduction Reimbursement</u></strong>: To help physicians spend their time advising patients about their health, we reimburse the following services:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Smoking Cessation Counseling, Alcohol and Substance Abuse Counseling</li>
          <li>&nbsp;Preventive Medicine Individual and Group Counseling</li>
        </ul>

