      <div class="generic-block">
        <h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>

        <ul class="unstyled expand-list">
          <li class="expand-group">
            <h3 class="expand-link"><span class="expand-toggle">[ + ]</span>What is a CO-OP?</h3>

            <div style="display: none;" class="expand-content">
              <p><span style="font-family: 'Avenir LT W01 45 Book', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px;">Health Republic Insurance of New York is a Consumer Operated and Oriented Plan, created under the Affordable Care Act. CO-OPs serve individuals and small businesses and those who have been traditionally underserved by the more established health carriers. Profits are invested in lower premiums or better benefits. In time, our Board will have a majority representation of people who actually have insurance from Health Republic. We are also encouraged to test innovations in health care coverage.</span></p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="expand-group">
            <h3 class="expand-link"><span class="expand-toggle">[ + ]</span>What is the primary physician concept?</h3>

            <div style="display: none;" class="expand-content">
              <p><span style="font-family: 'Avenir LT W01 45 Book', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px;">Although many people use the term “Primary Care Physician,” we believe the term “Primary Physician” better captures what most people need…a doctor who: </span></p>

              <ul>
                <li>understands them and their individual needs</li>
                <li>is available for questions and concerns</li>
                <li>stands at the center of a large array of services</li>
              </ul>
              We are incentivizing our members to select a Primary Physician and use that doctor for both preventive care and treatment. We will partner with the Primary Physicians as needed to support member health education, behavior change and analytics.

              <p>&nbsp;</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="expand-group">
            <h3 class="expand-link"><span class="expand-toggle">[ + ]</span>What is the network and when are referrals required?</h3>

            <div style="display: none;" class="expand-content">
              <p><span style="font-family: 'Avenir LT W01 45 Book', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px;">Health Republic Insurance of New York relies on MagnaCare for the foundation of its network. The MagnaCare network has been reviewed and approved by the New York State Department of Health to offer sufficient coverage in the counties we serve. It includes many of the state’s key hospitals. In addition to MagnaCare, Health Republic is contracting with community health centers and accountable care organizations, especially those with the infrastructure to support population management. Thus, we call our network “MagnaCare Extra.”</span></p>

              <p><span style="font-family: 'Avenir LT W01 45 Book', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px;">Health Republic Health plans do not have out of network benefits, thus all specialty services must be provided by clinicians in the Magnacare Extra network. In the rare instance that a patient requires a unique specialized service, please contact us directly. We do not require any referrals from the Primary Physician to access other services. However, please review and reference the Prior Approval lists (in the Important Resources section) to ensure that the use of medications and procedures follow our requirements. </span></p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="expand-group">
            <h3 class="expand-link"><span class="expand-toggle">[ + ]</span>How can a provider participate in your network?</h3>

            <div style="display: none;" class="expand-content">
              <p><span style="font-family: 'Avenir LT W01 45 Book', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px;">For most specialty and ancillary providers, we partner with MagnaCare to build our network. To assure faster service, please call them directly at 888.624.6202.</span></p>

              <p><span style="font-family: 'Avenir LT W01 45 Book', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px;">Community health centers, patient centered medical homes, and accountable care organizations may call our Provider Relations Department at 646.679.4575. </span></p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="expand-group">
            <h3 class="expand-link"><span class="expand-toggle">[ + ]</span>Do you cover complementary and alternative care (CAM)?</h3>

            <div style="display: none;" class="expand-content">
              <p><span style="font-family: 'Avenir LT W01 45 Book', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px;">Beyond the required chiropractic coverage and a select number of acupuncture visits for certain diagnoses, Health Republic Insurance of New York does not provide CAM benefits. However, our members can access CAM providers through Healthways WholeHealth Living, where they can search and select credentialed providers, all of whom will provide a discount on their fees to our members.</span></p>

              <p><span style="font-family: 'Avenir LT W01 45 Book', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 22px;">With limited exceptions CAM is not included in the benefit designs of HRI NY Products; Chiropractic is a covered benefit. Acupuncture is a covered benefit for Primary Select and Primary Select EPO products. </span></p>
            </div>
          </li>
